<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Discussion.</emphasis>
this species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fairchild" box="[671,853,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" refString="Fairchild, G. B. (1964) Notes on Neotropical Tabanidae (Diptera). IV. Further new species and new records for Panama. Journal of Medical Entomology, 1 (2), 169 - 185." type="journal article" year="1964">
Fairchild (
<number box="[786,844,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from only one specimen which had no locality data, deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[357,441,189,212]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">BMNH</collectionCode>
(fig. 
<number box="[516,531,188,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="6.0">6</number>
C). Even with this difficulty, Fairchild had no doubts about publishing the description: “The specimen is beautifully preserved and in spite of having no locality, is so distinct and so obviously related to 
<taxonomicName box="[379,561,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Pseudelaphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellicornis">
<emphasis box="[379,407,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Ps</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[420,561,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">patellicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that I have felt it worth while to describe it.” The distinction mentioned by the author refers mainly to the conspicuous wing spot, indicated by the specific epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1205,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Pseudelaphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigribasis">
<emphasis box="[1093,1205,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">nigribasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has not been observed in any other 
<taxonomicName box="[408,517,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Pityocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,517,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="314">Pityocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Fairchild did not publish any illustration with the original description; they are presented for the first time in this paper (figs. 
<number box="[666,680,367,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="314" value="6.0">6</number>
A–B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
